<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-09-21T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-09-21T21:00:00-05:00" n="49" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d49">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00116 European War 1939/555:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Winant</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-09-21T22:00:00-04:00">September 21, 1942—10
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>4588. From Hopkins. With reference to your telegram no. 5253,<note n="31" xml:id="d49fn31"><hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> your August
                            5th letter has just reappeared after having been mislaid. I am in
                            agreement with you that no direct or indirect reference ought to be made
                            to the Bryce Committee. I hope you will receive word very soon on this
                            matter which has been turned over to the State Department.
                            [Hopkins.]</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>